<ABS>  China: Energy </ABS>
<DATE1>   23 November 1993 </DATE1>
<F P=100> THERMAL POWER </F>
<H3> <TI>   Huangjuezhuang No. 1 Unit Joins Grid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P60078A Chengdu SICHUAN RIBAO in Chinese 23 Nov 93 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 94P60078A </F>
<F P=104>  Chengdu SICHUAN RIBAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] On 21 November, the 200-kilowatt No. 1 generator of 
Sichuan's Huangjuezhuang power plant--a major construction 
project of the Eighth Five-Year Plan--joined the grid for the 
first time. 
  The Huangjuezhuang power plant will have a total installed 
capacity of 1.2 million kilowatts. In the first stage of 
construction, two 200MW coal-fired units will be installed; the 
project is a joint investment construction effort on the part of 
the State and Sichuan Province. Construction officially began in 
November 1991. The No. 1 unit was among the units that would 
give the nation an increase of 12,000MW in 1993. The No. 1 unit 
will help to ease Sichuan's energy shortage and promote the 
province's economic growth. 
  The plant's No. 2 unit could be finished and could begin 
generating power by June 1994. 

</TEXT>

