<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Payments System To Be Unified With Krajinas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1502102194 Belgrade POLITIKA in Serbo-Croatian 11 Feb 94 p 
13 </F>

<F P=103> AU1502102194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade POLITIKA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by D.K.: "New Dinar in the Srpska Republic and the </F>
Republic of Serbian Krajina"] 
  [Text] Banja Luka, 10 February -- On the territory of the 
Srpska republic and the republic of Serbian Krajina a unified 
payment operations' system with Serbia, that is to say, of the 
two Krajinas with Yugoslavia, is supposed to come into effect on 
Monday, it was announced at today's meeting of prime ministers 
and departmental ministers of the Srpska republic and the 
republic of Serbian Krajina [RSK], held in Banja Luka. Prime 
Minister of the Srpska republic Vladimir Lukic and RSK Prime 
Minister Djordje Bjegovic confirmed at a news conference that 
the new dinar should be officially introduced into payment 
operations, which will be unified among the Serbian lands in the 
shortest possible time. 
  According to the latest information, the text of a protocol 
has just been completed in Belgrade, to which, among others, the 
National Bank of Yugoslavia has also given its consent. It is 
thus expected that as of Monday the new dinar will also be the 
official means of payment between Krajinas and the FRY [Federal 
Republic of Yugoslavia]. There will be no more postponements, as 
this would incur great losses to both Krajinas. 

</TEXT>

