<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Koljevic Deems Peaceful Border Changes Possible </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20377C Belgrade VECERNJE NOVOSTI in Serbo-Croatian 31 Jan 
94 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> 94P20377C </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade VECERNJE NOVOSTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by Sl.P.: "Peaceful Change of Borders?"] </F>
  [Text] Dr. Nikola Koljevic, member of the presidency of the 
republic of Srpska, stated yesterday in an interview with the 
Zagreb weekly GLOBUS that "I think the resolution of the events 
in the republic of Serbian Krajina is to follow soon as 
intensive efforts are being made to correct overall Serbian- 
Croatian relations. And there are several ways to achieve the 
resolution. If Serbian and Croatian peoples were to act with 
maturity, they could achieve a historical agreement." 
  According to Dr. Koljevic, based on this "historical 
agreement" it would be possible to begin peaceful changes of 
borders. 
  "Alternately, it might also be possible to reach the 
agreement to give some kind of a very high political autonomy to 
the Serbs in Krajina, guaranteed by the Republic of Croatia. In 
any event, it would take a long time for people to accept this. 
I believe that economic activities will revive with time to 
contribute to a more rational resolution of problems." 

</TEXT>

