<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Socialist Party Statement on Bosnia Policy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20413B Zagreb VJESNIK in Serbo-Croatian 10 Feb 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> 94P20413B </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb VJESNIK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> ["SSH Public Statement"] </F>
  [Text] The SSH [Socialist Party of Croatia] leadership 
distributed the following public statement at a news conference: 
  1) The Republic of Croatia must immediately and clearly, 
without any reservations, declare its support for a unified 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, which should not be divided on an ethnic 
basis. 
  2) The Republic of Croatia must make a clear and unambiguous 
statement that it will strive to protect, with all means except 
military ones, those elements of the Croatian nation who live 
outside the republic's borders. 
  3) The Croatian people -- a substantial part of whom gave 
their votes of confidence to the HDZ [Croatian Democratic 
Community] at the last elections -- did not vote for a policy of 
war and military engagement in other countries. They must be 
informed of all the relevant factors that have led to the 
growing international isolation of Croatia and the threat of 
international sanctions. 
  4) The introduction of sanctions against Croatia would be 
counterproductive, as confirmed by the case of Serbia, and they 
must be avoided in the interest of the majority of the 
population which would be hardest hit. 

</TEXT>

