<H3> <TI>   New Resignations at SLOBODNA DALMACIJA </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20413A Zagreb VJESNIK in Serbo-Croatian 8 Feb 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> 94P20413A </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb VJESNIK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] (HINA) Split -- On Monday [7 February], Dr. Goran 
Dodig, a member of the Board of Directors of the SLOBODNA 
DALMACIJA Newspaper, Inc., handed his irrevocable resignation to 
Miroslav Kutle, president of the Shareholders' Assembly, and 
director Ante Busic, stating: "I would like to inform you that I 
have decided to terminate my participation in the work of the 
Board beginning 6 February 1994. I wish you much success in your 
future endeavors." 
  Metod Jurisic, president of the Board of Directors, had 
resigned before Dodig, citing disagreements with the editorial 
policy of the editor in chief. Dodig and Jurisic had been 
members of the Board of Directors since the transformation and 
privatization of SLOBODNA DALMACIJA. 

</TEXT>

