<H3> <TI>   Croatian Company Wins Russian Contract </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20371B Split SLOBODNA DALMACIJA in Serbo-Croatian 1 Feb 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> 94P20371B </F>
<F P=104>  Split SLOBODNA DALMACIJA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by Sa. Paparella: "INA Is Building in Vladivostok"] </F>
  [Text] Zagreb--At a ceremony held on Monday [31 January] in 
the offices of the INA enterprise, Franjo Greguric, general 
director of the company, signed a $130-million agreement with 
Nikolaj M. Shubenichev, general director of the Far Eastern 
Petroleum Company of Vladivostok, on the construction of berths 
for tankers at Kamchatka and facilities at the oil pipeline 
terminal for loading oil into the tankers. 
  The "turnkey" agreement calls for the construction of an 
ecologically acceptable terminal with a total annual loading 
capacity of 4.2 million metric tons of oil derivatives with an 
accompanying reservoir area of 300,000 cubic meters over a 
period of 30 months. INA is responsible for the organization and 
the oversight of the work, and Montmontaza of Zagreb, tasked 
with carrying out projects in which over 500 workers will 
participate, is the most important of numerous Croatian 
subcontractors. The signing of the contract was a great success 
because of strong international competition. INA won the 
contract on the basis of the good quality of the projects it has 
carried out in Russia to date. 

</TEXT>

