<F P=100> SLOVENIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Danica Draskovic Blasts Serbian Leadership </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20359A Ljubljana DNEVNIK in Slovene 3 Feb 94 p 9 </F>
<F P=103> 94P20359A </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana DNEVNIK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovene </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by T.M.: "Danica Mad at Serbian Leadership"] </F>
  [Text] Belgrade, 3 February -- The Serbian opposition 
magazine SRPSKA REC published a scathing criticism of Serbian 
policy written by its director Danica Draskovic, wife of 
opposition leader Vuk Draskovic. She said that there is no 
doubt about who is responsible for the war in Bosnia, that 
weapons and ammunition are manufactured in Serbia, and that 
everything began because certain people wanted to grab power. 
The accusations are directed at Radovan Karadzic and his 
associates. Danica Draskovic asks what were the reasons for the 
war, since nobody had persecuted Serbs. She compares this 
situation to Germany in 1945. At that time too, many Germans 
insisted that they had no knowledge about camps and graves. She 
believes that many Serbs will maintain the same after a year or 
two when everything will be over. 
  Danica Draskovic also accuses the Serbian Red Cross of 
arbitrarily distributing foreign humanitarian aid. This cannot 
be concealed, she adds, since even the most progovernment media 
admit that 75 percent disappears without a trace. She promises 
to inform all humanitarian organizations that the aid meant for 
the poorest and most suffering people ends up on the black 
market controlled by the Serbian authorities. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

