<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Food Manufacturers Warn of Spring Sowing Problems </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1402164094 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1402164094 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Spring Sowing Uncertain"] </F>
  [Text] Food manufacturers announce, as early as now, a 
lack of finances for the spring sowing. The selective program, 
the previous sole source of finances for this and other 
agricultural activities, will definitely be abolished on March 
31. The approved finances by the National Bank of Macedonia -- 
a total of 140 million denars -- are aimed only for financing 
the production of corn. The stabilization program restrictions 
even more limit the possibilities of any additional sources. 
Thus, changes will have to be introduced in the plans for 
sowing of 218,140 hectares with rice, sugar beet, sunflower, and 
other products. 

</TEXT>

