<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Data on Herceg-Bosna Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20435A Split SLOBODNA DALMACIJA in Serbo-Croatian 18 Feb 
94 p 6 </F>

<F P=103> 94P20435A </F>
<F P=104>  Split SLOBODNA DALMACIJA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Report by HINA: "Biography of Zubak"] </F>
  [Text] Kresimir Zubak, president of the presidential 
council of the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna, was born on 29 
November 1947 in Doboj and is a lawyer by training. 
  He entered the political life of the Croat republic of 
Herceg-Bosna as a representative of the Croatian Defense Council 
of Usora. Before the war he carried out duties in judicial 
bodies. Immediately before the outbreak of the war he was 
president of the Supreme Court in Doboj. He has served as vice 
president of the Croatian Community of Herceg-Bosna -- as it was 
called at that time -- and was later elected minister of justice 
and administration of the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna. 

</TEXT>

