<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   NATO-Compatible Encoding System Developed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20442A </F>
<F P=103> 94P20442A </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:CSO 

  [Editorial Report] The development of a new Polish 
encryption system for military communications that is compatible 
with NATO secure communications systems was reported in a 28 
February Polish television news broadcast. According to TV 
Polonia's "Wiadomosci" program, the new digital system will 
permit the transmission of encoded messages by telephone and 
radio within the Polish military and government, as well as to 
compatible foreign systems. The development of the encryption 
system was financed by the Ministry of National Defense and the 
Committee for Scientific Research. Deputy Communications 
Minister Marek Rusin told "Wiadomosci" that "this system is 
three times cheaper than similar ones used in the West, and its 
quality is competitive with NATO standards." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

